meanings.definition: The state or quality of being superior or outstanding.
meanings.sent1: Her supereminence in academics earned her the top student award.
meanings.sent2: The supereminence of the mountain peak made it a popular hiking destination.
meanings.sent3: The cat believed her supereminence in napping was unmatched by any other pet.
meanings.sent4: The supereminence of the sun in the sky reminded him of his own potential to shine brightly.
meanings.sent5: The supereminence of the diamond sparkled in the sunlight, capturing everyone's attention.

meanings.sent1: He worked hard to achieve the supereminence of team captain.
meanings.sent2: The company's supereminence in the industry was well-known.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel claimed the supereminence of the tallest tree branch as his own throne.
meanings.sent4: The supereminence of the eagle soaring high symbolized freedom and strength.
